   <category name='gifts'>

      <section name='keyring'>

         <para number='1' comment='keyring'>
         is carrying a multi-dimensional keyring made by the prestigious TenBrane Corp. If you look carefully you can see the glow of the macro-superstring logo. It has on it:
         </para>

         <para number='2' comment='Washroom key'>
         The ornate key is a much sought after key to the Galactic Administration executive washroom, and is genetically coded to its owner.
         </para>

         <para number='3' comment='2005 valentine'>
         You can see a small red valentine heart with the number 2005 etched into it.
         </para>

         <para number='4' comment='staff key fob 2005'>
         The key fob carries the writing 'Fed2 Staff 2005'.
         </para>

         <para number='5' comment='croquet mallet'>
         You can see a miniature croquet mallet cunningly carved so that it also appears to be a tiny pink flamingo.
         </para>

         <para number='6' comment='silver shamrock'>
         The shamrock is an exquisitely wrought silver keyring accessory.
         </para>

         <para number='7' comment='Jester for 2005'>
         You can see a square cut Venusian diamond. At its heart a tiny holo of a jester juggles balls, turns cartwheels and performs fire eating tricks for your entertainment. In tiny letters on the edge of the plinth on which he is performing is the number '2005'.
         </para>

         <para number='8' comment='Maypole for 2005'>
         The maypole is a marvel of miniature engineering. Tiny figures holding the ribbons dance round it as you watch. Power is supplied by the keyring, and etched into the pole, just visible, is the number 2005.
         </para>

         <para number='9' comment='Class of 2005 scroll'>
         The scroll, engraved with the words 'Class of 2005', is an exquisitely wrought white gold keyring accessory.
         </para>

         <para number='10' comment='2005 tarot card'>
         The tiny tarot card is made of burnished gunmetal depicting a highly stylized sun on the obverse. The reverse side is an art deco geometric design with the number 2005 in the center.
         </para>

         <para number='11' comment='liberty bell 2005'>
         The tiny replica of the Liberty Bell is made of bronze. If you look carefully you can see that it even has a crack down one side - just like the original. Stamped on the rim is the number 2005.
         </para>

         <para number='12' comment='laser lighter 2005'>
         This keyring accessory is a tiny laser BBQ lighter. The lighter is embossed with the number 2005 on one side, and Gallagher's logo on the other.
         </para>

         <para number='13' comment='magellan ship 2005'>
         This keyring accessory is a silver replica of Magellan's ship, the Victoria. Engraved on the sails are the numbers 1522 and 2005.
         </para>

         <para number='14' comment='Jack O Lantern'>
         The jack o lantern grins evilly at you. The light inside is powered by the keyring, and has been set to pulse in an odd, and rather unsettling, arrhythmic fashion. The number 2005 is imprinted on the back.
         </para>

         <para number='15' comment='Firework -2005'>
         As you touch it the firework emits a shower of multi-colored sparks which crackle and flash as they float away. The legend Diwali 2005 has been embossed into the side of the firework.
         </para>

         <para number='16' comment='Thanksgiving 2005'>
         You inadvertently squeeze the tiny rubber turkey, a 2005 special, and it immediately makes a farting noise the volume of which completely belies the size of the charm!
         </para>

         <para number='17' comment='Christmas Cracker 2005'>
         You examine the TenBrane Corp reverse-entropy Christmas cracker. There is a *BANG!* as it comes apart, and then, before your very eyes, the exploded parts drift back together to form a whole. On the side is an ornate number, 2005.
         </para>

         <para number='18' comment='staff star 2005'>
         The tiny star glitters with an intense blue-white light. It reminds you of Rigel seen from its fourth planet. Squinting slightly, and donning a pair of Raybans, you can make out lettering deep in the heart of the star - 'Fed2 staff 2005'.
         </para>

         <para number='19' comment='ming 2006 music box'>
         It starts to play Auld Lang Syne and a hologram appears with the numbers 2006. Suddenly they vanish and are replaced by a shadowy figure - it is the ex-Emperor Ming! He laughs maniacally, shouts "I'll be back" and then fades away.
         </para>

         <para number='20' comment='Jan 2006 charm'>
         This is one of the new 53 tera-quantel 'Box Brownie 2006' holo cameras. At the touch of a button the tiny camera expands to operating size, making it easy to use both camera and projector modes.
         </para>

         <para number='21' comment='Feb 2006 charm'>
         This Valentine rose is perfectly formed, with deep red petals that will never fade, droop or fall off. In the centre of the bloom, a small holo flashes the number '2006'.
         </para>

         <para number='22' comment='Mar 2006 charm'>
         This four-dimensional glass prism gathers in light and disperses it, sending rainbows spreading out in all directions. Every so often, the number '2006' flashes in amongst the seven bright colors.
         </para>

         <para number='23' comment='St Pat 2006 charm'>
         A tiny silver leprechaun clutching a pot of gold dances inside a silver cage, his little hat bouncing up and down as he sways from side to side doing a jig. The words 'St Patrick's Day 2006' are embroidered on his jacket.
         </para>

         <para number='24' comment='April 2006 charm'>
         Deep within the center of the faceted emerald, green lights flicker and flash in imitation of the Martian lights. From time to time, the brilliant flashes of lightning coalesce and form into the numbers '2006'.
         </para>

         <para number='25' comment='Easter 2006 charm'>
