      <section name='buy'>

         <para number='1'>
         "That's great," enthuses the droid. "Tell you what - I'll throw in a free shuttle and a half tank of fuel!" He plugs himself into a nearby terminal. "You're in luck, we have that model in your color in orbit at this moment. Please press a digit onto this pad to authorize the agreement and act as a key to the ship."
         </para>

         <para number='2'>
         You follow the droid's instructions and are the proud owner of a spaceship. (Well strictly speaking, the bank is the proud owner of your spaceship!) The shuttle awaits you on the landing pad.
         </para>

         <para number='3'>
         The droid's lips curl in a nasty sneer - they must be made of memory metal - and it looks at you down its olfactory sensor. "Forget it punk," it tells you. "You don't have enough groats to buy a used empty hull, let alone a functioning ship." With that it turns its back on you and opens a conversation with another prospect.
         </para>

         <para number='4'>
         An oily looking sales droid oozes up to you and tells you, "Have I got a deal for you! For just 200,000ig I can let you have one of our special reconditioned Harrier class starter ships. And that includes a loan to cover 100 percent of the cost! It's a steal at that price. So. Waddayasay? Yes or no?"
         </para>

